sentences: Aziz-Ur-Rahman Ibrahim (born 16 March 1964) is a British musician.
Ibrahim also provided the vocals for Weller's spoken word song entitled "God", on his 2008 album, 22 Dreams along with guitars for previous Paul Weller releases, e.g. Illumination.
Most notably, Ibrahim was the guitarist for the last Stone Roses performance before they split, at the 1996 Reading Festival.
In 2019 Aziz became patron of All Fm 96.9 community radio station in Manchester www.allfm.org
He performed on the Simply Red 1987/88 world tour but did not feature on the following album.
